{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pasta","content":["Place pasta flour, salt, spinach, egg and egg yolk in mixing bowl then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 6<b>. Knead <b>3 min\/<b>.","Wrap dough in cling film and leave to rest in fridge for 20-30 minutes. Meanwhile prepare filling."]},{"title":"Ricotta and Spinach Filling","content":["Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place shallots and butter in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add spinach and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b> whilst stirring with spatula through hole in mixing bowl lid.","Add ricotta, grated Parmesan and nutmeg then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Divide chilled dough into two pieces, then use a pasta machine or rolling pin to roll out each piece very thinly (1-2 mm). Cut out rounds with a pastry cutter (Ø 9 cm). Brush each round with egg white and place approx. 1 tsp filling in centre of each round.","Fold each pasta round over, enclosing filling and gently squeezing all the air out, then press firmly to seal edges together.","Bring a large pan of salted water to the boil. Once at a rolling boil, gently lower a few ravioli at a time into it using a slotted spoon, then cook 3-4 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon, then serve immediately with a drizzle of oil and a sprinkling of grated Parmesan."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pasta","content":["200 g pasta flour (00 flour)","1 pinch fine sea salt","50 g fresh spinach, washed and dried","1 egg, large","1 egg yolk, from large egg"]},{"title":"Ricotta and Spinach Filling","content":["60 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces","50 g shallots, quartered","15 g butter","300 g fresh spinach, washed and dried","120 g ricotta cheese","1 pinch ground nutmeg"]},{"title":"Cooking","content":["semolina, fine, for dusting","1 egg white, for brushing","water, for cooking pasta","1 tsp fine sea salt","olive oil, for serving"]}],"id":"r85268","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-9u-mL_jUkqQ\/XZQGbw42ovI\/AAAAAAAAb-A\/XVG_nz4G1sUKh2XWdPAwKwmaZ4nks8dQQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_PU31a0GChytQvITN.png","title":"Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli","publishedAt":"2015-08-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"21.3 g","fat":"16.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"40 g","calories":"1632 kJ \/ 390 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, pastry brush, round pastry cutter, rolling pin or pasta machine, slotted spoon, saucepan, refrigerator, hob","hintsAndTricks":["If pasta dough still looks like crumbs after mixing in step 1 add water, 1 tsp at a time, and mix a few seconds more at speed 6 until dough begins to cling together."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h","1h 30m","4 portions"]}